-- REFILE-BSkyB H1 revenues meet forecasts, profits up
-- 
-- Wed Jan 31, 2007 2:18am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/31/bskyb-results-idUSWLB425720070131

 

  (Restores dropped word 'percent' in first paragraph) 


  
 LONDON  Jan 31 (Reuters) - British pay-TV firm BSkyB Plc
( BSY.L ) met forecasts with a 10 percent rise in first-half
revenues to 2.2 billion pounds ($4.32 billion) on Wednesday
while pretax profit was up strongly at 356 million pounds.  The company said it had added 183,000 net TV subscribers in
the second quarter, below the average forecast of 190,000 in a
Reuters poll of 11 analysts.  BSkyB, which launched a broadband service last July, said it
had connected 193,000 customers in the first half, or by the end
of December, and had 259,000 customers by the end of January.


